The aforementioned purchase of the surplus goods from the Surplus Property Commission by Villa-Abrille was subsequently investigated by Provincial Revenue Agent H.I. Bernardo, who, on April 1, 1953, submitted his report (Annex E) to petitioner, on the basis of which report, petitioner made the following assessment, against respondent on January 27, 1955:




Total sales subject to 5%


Sales from August, 1948 to Sept. 6, 1950 (with invoices) 
P133,653.42


Sales with deed of sales, 1949 ........................................ 
27,000.00


Total ....................................................................................... 
P160,655.42


5% on P160, 655.42 ........................................................... 
P8,032.77
